\subsection{Leveled heading-frame acceleration}

The direction estimator uses inertial acceleration in a leveled frame aligned
with boat heading: $+X$ forward, $+Y$ starboard, and $+Z$ up. Body-frame
specific force is rotated to NED, gravity is restored, and horizontal
acceleration is projected onto the bow and starboard axes. This removes
roll--pitch gravity mixing while retaining boat-relative azimuth. Invalid
attitude or an undefined projected bow heading produces no direction output
rather than a raw body-frame fallback.
